# Privacy Policy

**Effective date:** March 29, 2026

Tic Tac Toe Online: XO Game ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect information when you use our mobile application.

## 1. Information We Collect

### 1.1 Information You Provide

When you use the app, we may collect information you provide directly, including:

- Name or display name
- Email address, if you sign in with email or Google
- Profile image, if you upload one
- Support messages or contact details you provide

### 1.2 Information Collected Automatically

We may automatically collect certain information related to your use of the app, including:

- Device information
- App version
- Authentication status
- Gameplay activity
- Leaderboard score, coins, skins, game history, and multiplayer activity
- Advertising interaction data
- Purchase status for in-app products

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

- Create and manage your account
- Enable guest login, Google sign in, and email login
- Save game progress, coins, skins, profile data, and history
- Support multiplayer matchmaking and gameplay features
- Display leaderboards and player statistics
- Process rewards, ads, and in-app purchases
- Improve app performance, security, and stability
- Prevent abuse, fraud, and unauthorized activity

## 3. Authentication and Account Data

The app may allow sign in through guest login, Google Sign-In, and email/password authentication. When you sign in, account-related information may be processed through third-party authentication providers such as Google and Firebase Authentication.

## 4. Multiplayer and Gameplay Data

To provide online gameplay features, we may store and process game-related data such as player identity, opponent matching, game room details, results, move history, and leaderboard statistics.

## 5. Profile Images and User Content

If you upload a profile image or other allowed content, that content may be stored through cloud services used by the app. You are responsible for ensuring that any content you upload does not infringe the rights of others.

## 6. In-App Purchases

The app may offer digital items such as coins, skins, rewards, or similar virtual content. Purchases are processed by the platform provider, such as Google Play, and we do not collect or store your full payment card information.

## 7. Advertising

The app may show ads and may provide rewards for watching eligible ads. Advertising services may collect limited technical and usage information in accordance with their own privacy policies.

## 8. Third-Party Services

The app may use third-party services, including but not limited to:

- Firebase Authentication
- Firebase Realtime Database
- Firebase Storage
- Google Play Billing
- Google Mobile Ads
- Unity Ads
- Google Sign-In

These services may collect, process, and store data according to their own privacy policies.

## 9. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited information only when necessary to:

- Provide core app functionality
- Process authentication, cloud storage, ads, or purchases
- Comply with legal obligations
- Protect our rights, users, or services

## 10. Data Retention

We retain data for as long as necessary to provide app functionality, maintain accounts, resolve disputes, enforce our policies, and comply with legal obligations. We may remove inactive or unnecessary data at our discretion.

## 11. Children’s Privacy

The app is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children in violation of applicable law. If you believe a child has provided personal information without appropriate consent, please contact us so we can review and take appropriate action.

## 12. Security

We take reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to help protect your information. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

## 13. Your Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding access, correction, or deletion of your personal information. You may also request account-related changes by contacting us through the support details provided in the app or store listing.

## 14. International Data Processing

Your information may be processed and stored on servers located outside your country or region, depending on the infrastructure used by our service providers.

## 15. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updated versions will be posted with a revised effective date. Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the updated Privacy Policy.

## 16. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us using the support email or contact details provided in the app listing or developer profile.
